#: ../../en/topology_topo_types.rst:165
msgid ""
"Each schema topology can have its own relation's table, it will be "
"created when you create your first TopoGeometry, the table is stored "
"inside the topology as ``custom_topology.relation``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../en/topology_topo_types.rst:167
msgid ""
"Each row of the table is called a \"Component\", like a component of the "
"relations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../en/topology_topo_types.rst:169
msgid ""
"The component saves pairs of two things, a TopoGeometry Key and a "
"TopoElement, remember that each TopoElement can only represent one "
"Primitive or TopoGeometry, so for a TopoGeometry be able to represent "
"several of them the tables stores multiple rows with the same "
"TopoGeometry Key and different TopoElements, this way only filtering in "
"the table we can get all the TopoElements for any TopoGeometry."
